                {
                  "key": "response",
                  "value": {
                    "stringValue": "## Summary — APA-43311 implemented\n\n- **`extractor/writer.py`**: added `append_csv_row()` (creates `records.csv` with a header if it doesn't exist, appends otherwise) and wired it into `write_record()` via a new optional `csv_path` param — the CSV append only happens when a JSON file is actually newly written, so it's idempotent for free (no separate dedup logic needed).\n- **`extractor/cli.py`**: added `--csv-path` flag, defaulting to `<output>\\records.csv`.\n- **CSV schema**: same 12 output fields in the same order, plus `Request ID` for traceability back to the JSON file.\n- **Tests**: added `tests/test_writer.py` (5 tests) — full suite now 23 tests, all passing.\n- **Verified against real data**: full run produced `extracted\\records.csv` with exactly 28 lines (1 header + 27 rows, matching the 27 JSON files). Re-running the CLI wrote 0 new JSON files and the CSV stayed at 28 lines — confirmed idempotent.\n\nUntouched, as scoped: `otlp_flatten.py`, `jira.py`, `agent.py`, `correlate.py`, `state_store.py`."
                  },
